      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOWRIDER (4) is a lightly-raced but progressive colt who hails from a leading yard. Raced just twice at the maiden campaign, winning here on debut before a second in a Vicbred heat. That was back in November but he is likely to have developed with maturity and was readied with a handy trial. Well placed for a winning return. SECRET SERVICE AGENT NZ (8) is racing well having led to score well at this circuit and distance before placing at Geelong last time. Draws for a trail so can perform well again. KEAYANG SEASIDE (5) continued her consistent form from last campaign when she came from the back row to place at Terang. That was her first outing for 10 months so it should have improved her and she won her lone second-up attempt. BULLETPROOF KID (7) made an encouraging return after three-and-a-half months when he led and stuck on for a 1.3m third at Cranbourne. Draws much wider but should strip fitter.",
